            <TextArea editable="false" maxHeight="1.7976931348623157E308" maxWidth="1.7976931348623157E308" text="Gameplay Objective:&#10;The goal is to sink all of your opponent's ships before they sink yours.&#10;&#10;Ship Placement:&#10;- Players take turns to place their ships on a 10x10 grid.&#10;- Ships can be placed horizontally or vertically, but they cannot overlap.&#10;- Each player has 5 ships of varying lengths: &#10;    - Carrier (5)  &#10;    - Battleship (4)  &#10;    - Cruiser (3)  &#10;    - Submarine (3)  &#10;    - Destroyer (2)&#10;&#10;Attack Phase:&#10;- Players alternate turns to attack a cell on the opponent's grid.&#10;- A successful hit will mark the cell as hit, while a miss will mark the cell as missed.&#10;- The round ends when a player misses a shot or uses an ultimate ability.&#10;&#10;Winning the Game:&#10;- The game ends when all of one player's ships have been sunk.&#10;- The player who sinks all of their opponent's ships first wins the game.&#10;&#10;Ultimate Abilities (Unlocks When):&#10;    - There have been a total of 5 misses.&#10;    - Player has made 5 hits.&#10;    - Player has made 20 shots.&#10;    - Player has sunk 3 ships.&#10;    - Player has 3 sunken ships.&#10;&#10;Game Rounds:&#10;- Players alternate turns, each round allowing one attack unless an ultimate ability is used.&#10;- Rounds continue until one player wins by sinking all of the opponent's ships.&#10;&#10;Additional Rules:&#10;- A player's ultimate ability button is disabled at the start of the game and only becomes available when specific conditions are met.&#10;- All buttons on the grid are temporarily disabled during the execution of an ultimate ability to prevent additional actions during the attack." GridPane.halignment="CENTER" GridPane.rowIndex="1" GridPane.valignment="CENTER">
